<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Visiting information</h3>
<p>Standard visiting times for adult wards – from 3pm to 4pm and evening visiting usually between 6:30pm – 8pm. Visitors are advised to contact the ward directly for specific times. Visits may be allowed out of hours in exceptional circumstances, at the ward manager’s discretion. <br/><br/>Maternity wards, children's wards and critical care units have their own visiting rules - details are available directly from the wards.<br/><br/>The number of visitors at the bedside should not exceed two.<br/><br/>Visitors are asked to use the alcohol gel hand rub that is provided on entering and leaving a ward.</p>
